Alternatively, you could use bubble sort:

```python
def sort_array(arr):
    n = len(arr)

    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
    return arr

array = [3, 7, 2, 1, 6]
sorted_array = sort_array(array)
```

In both cases, the input array [3, 7, 2, 1, 6] will be sorted in ascending order to produce the output [1, 2, 3, 6, 7].

